Thinking about a change? 

The Digital & Data Engineering division brings together the teams who enable EllisDon to leverage technology in every aspect of its business, to push beyond traditional industry positions and drive change. Our objective is simple: to be leaders in technology just as we are leaders in building. Our core values empower people to deliver great careers to one another and develop creative solutions for complex problems for our Cradle To Grave Services, Construction operation and our clients. We are a group of professionals with a variety of expertise within software engineering, product management, data management and analytics, professional services, virtual design, construction, and IT operations.

Above all, we are a group of individuals with unique experiences, and, at EllisDon, we choose to celebrate the strength in our differences, every day. EllisDon’s commitment to Inclusive Diversity is to work together to create an environment where every employee feels safe to be their true and authentic self. Ultimately, EllisDon’s purpose is to provide people with similar values the opportunity to achieve to their full potential; to deliver that opportunity for great careers to one another; and to contribute meaningfully to the community we share with others. 


You as a Data Analyst (Insight and Analytics) will:
Apply your knowledge of quantitative and programmatic methods; expertise with data analysis tools and techniques; and critical-thinking skills to derive actionable information from data;
Distill complex relationships and large amounts of data into intuitive, informative, and descriptive reports and dashboards that will be used to empower product teams and guide business decisions;
Drive the continuous improvement and overall state of data governance and quality across the organization, while leveraging technology (Informatica) to augment metadata, governance, and stewardship initiatives;
Partner with business and product stakeholders to assist in the identification and documentation of business and data usage requirements, processes, needs, and key performance indicators;
Collaborate with product development teams to influence the delivery of innovative data-driven products/features by undertaking data-centric activities;
Draw on your extensive experience and expertise to contribute towards the development and enhancement of best practices in key areas of data analysis, data warehousing, and data management;
Conduct a variety of data-related activities which will contribute towards the enablement of self-service reporting and Bi capabilities for non-technical business stakeholders;
 Is this the right role for you?
Degree in Mathematics, Statistics, Engineering, Computer Science, or Data Science. Minimum five (5) years of industry experience in a data management, analysis, and/or business/data analyst role(s).
Expert-level proficiency and extensive experience with the following:
Data Analysis: SQL, NoSQL, Python, Excel;
Business Intelligence: Tableau, PowerBI, and/or DundasBI;
Data-Warehousing: Integrate (ETL/ELT), Manage (Schema Design), Query, Analyze.
Data Governance and Quality: Informatica (Axon, EDC, IDQ) or similar.
Practical working knowledge of the following areas:
Agile Development Methodologies;
Data Architecture;
Cloud Services: (Google Cloud Platform, Azure, AWS);
Project Management Tools: JIRA, Wrike;
Demonstrated experience solving business problems using quantitative analysis;
Working knowledge of construction-related best practices and processes an asset;
 EllisDon is proud to provide this unique career opportunity that provides continuous learning, opportunity for growth, and a competitive compensation package within an environment that is committed to inclusion and respects diversity.          

Go ahead and be yourself. We'll pay you for it! 

We are an equal opportunity employer. We welcome people of any age, culture, subculture, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, nationality, ethnicity, race, size, mental or physical status, veteran status, religion, language, political opinion, working-style preference, family status, education, and socio-economic status. The EllisDon core values of Integrity and Mutual Respect welcomes everyone, at work and in the community, and our value of Mutual Accountability, means that we all have a role to play. As an EllisDon employee, this will ultimately be your commitment to Inclusive Diversity. 
Accommodation for Applicants with disabilities will be made during the recruitment process when requested. 

We are committed to providing a positive candidate experience and ensuring timely updates are provided to all candidates. If you haven’t already, be sure to create a profile on our Careers page here to remain up to date on the status of your application and learn about new career opportunities as they arise.

With over 172,9 billion in assets under management as of March 31 2021, Fiera Capital, an independent firm, is one of Canada’s leading investment managers. We deliver customized multi-asset solutions across public and private market asset classes to institutional, financial intermediary and private wealth clients across North America, Europe and key markets in Asia. We strive to be at the forefront of investment-management science, and we are passionate about creating sustainable wealth for clients. Fiera Capital is recognized for our talented people. Our teams collaborate and seek to draw on the global industry’s most innovative and diverse offerings to craft strategies that meet the needs of any client, anywhere they are located.

Why Join Fiera Capital

Inclusive workplace and diverse background of employees
Growth and development opportunities
Entrepreneurial industry-leading company with a purposeful mission
Flexible work arrangements, competitive compensation and benefits
Collaborative approach, innovative and culture of integrity
Ambitious organization who strives for excellence

What We Are Looking For

The Data Analyst, Global Distribution Support will be a key part of the distribution team and will focus their efforts on robust ways to automate the internal collection and external communication of various quantitative elements required as part of our client service and business development efforts. The role will be part of the broader Global Distribution Support Group and will require interacting with various divisions within Fiera including risk, operations and investment teams. The incumbent will be well versed in systems used in asset management firms and will bring to the role an ability to think creatively to come up with solutions to new problems. The incumbent will be asked to analyze and project manage new initiatives such as implementing new internal procedures, systems and recommending the use of new technologies.

Your Responsibilities



Within the framework of his or her duties, the incumbent will perform the following tasks:
Automate data collection, aggregation and validation across the distribution platform;
Participate in the regular updates of quantitative data on external databases;
Lead special projects with a focus on data integrity and methods of streamlining processes;
Work closely with the RFP and Distribution teams as well as investment teams across Fiera to respond to client and prospect requests for quantitative information;
Develop tools (dashboards) for various stakeholders in the distribution business.

Must Have Requirements To Be Successful In This Role
University diploma in business administration, mathematics, computer science or a related field (finance, accounting, economics, etc.);
Master’s degree in business analytics, data science or a related field, an asset.
3-5 years of relevant experience, particularly in the investment sector, a portfolio management company, a consulting firm, a pension plan or an equivalent employer;
Strong Microsoft Office skills, especially Excel, PowerPoint and Power BI;
Programming proficiency in SQL and at least one of: Python, VBA, R;
Incredible attention to detail and strong analytical skills;
Project management skills;
Strong interest in financial markets and portfolio management;
Knowledge of Bloomberg;
Resourceful, self-sufficient, precise and a team player;
Proficiency in French and English (spoken and written) is an asset.
The use of masculine is for the sole purpose of lightening the text and refers to both women and men.

Fiera Capital subscribes to the principle of employment equity. Our staff is our most valuable asset and our goal is to create an inclusive and equitable environment where everyone can reach their true potential.

Fiera Capital will not tolerate any form of discrimination or harassment. All staffing decisions, including hiring and promotion decisions, will be based on merit, skills, performance and business needs. We are pleased to receive nominations from qualified individuals from a variety of backgrounds.

We thank all applicants for their interest in a career with Fiera Capital. We will only communicate with those selected for an interview.

