Company Description

Creating the unknown since 1997. At Ubisoft Montreal, we’re united by a common goal: to enrich players’ lives with original and memorable gaming experiences. We develop iconic franchises that engage millions around the world, like Assassin’s Creed, Far Cry, For Honor, Rainbow Six, Watch Dogs – and, well, we can’t disclose all our secrets just yet.

Our biggest strength is – and always will be – our people: the immensely talented team members surrounding, supporting, and producing the high-quality games that have made our studio what it is today.

When you join Ubi MTL, you’ll discover a workplace that sparks inspiration and connection: an environment with a variety of voices, identities, backgrounds, experiences, and perspectives. We offer a collaborative space that provides career advancement, a host of learning opportunities, and meaningful benefits centred on well-being.

Here, our shared desire to dream big, take risks, and constantly improve contributes to the innovation and boundary-pushing that ultimately leads to our collective success.

Job Description

You will join the Customer and Marketing Solutions department as a Business Analyst to strengthen the team responsible for CRM - Marketing Automation tools including Salesforce Marketing Cloud and internal solutions. The CRM team is split between Paris, Montreal, Bucharest and San Francisco and works in Agile mode.

You will be the link between the business and technical teams to transform business needs into effective and sustainable solutions. You will have to create a strong proximity with our business lines such as Operational Marketing, Strategic Marketing, Web and others. You will also have to build close links with different IT teams such as the Data or BI team.

This also implies testing solutions, validating them, documenting them and presenting them to stakeholders.

In This Capacity, Your Main Missions Will Be To
Analyze and investigate the needs of business teams;
Lead or participate in workshops to gather requirements;
Translate business needs into technical and functional specifications;
Validate specifications with developers and architects;
Develop and apply test cases to ensure the proper functioning of data flows;
Perform SQL queries to extract data;
Participate in project documentation and knowledge sharing with users;
Participate in user support.
Qualifications

Skills

Required
Good knowledge of the various Salesforce Marketing cloud modules;
Ability to analyze and translate a business need into functional specifications - thoroughness and attention to detail;
Good communication skills, and ability to collaborate with business partners;
Good command of SQL in query creation and data extraction;
Comfortable with data manipulation and audience creation;
Bilingualism in French and English is required in both spoken and written form.
Additional Information

Just a heads up: If you require a work permit, your eligibility may depend on your education and years of relevant work experience, as required by the government.

Skills

and competencies show up in different forms and can be based on different experiences, that's why we strongly encourage you to apply even though you may not have all the requirements listed above.

At Ubisoft, you can come as you are. We embrace diversity in all its forms. We’re committed to fostering a work environment that is inclusive and respectful of all differences.

